In article <aqWqjqtC8miL064yn@panix.com>,
Kevin Martin <cannon@panix.com> wrote:
> Nevertheless, it's worth a try. Check your kill file -- the only time 
> you see his deathless prose should be when someone else quotes it to 
> you.  Send them *polite* e-mail, once, asking them not to do that. 
> If they agree, fine, if not, ^K them too and be firm about it.

No need to ask other people to change.  Just use this trn kill file line:

    /^From: strnlght@netcom\.com /h:T,

Any posting by him will cause a line to be added to your kill file that
kills it and all followups.  Simple, reliable, and pretty fast with all
the hashing trn does.
